   &UR; INTERNATIONAL _ (Moved in ``i'' category)  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   FIRST-DAWN (Gisborne, New Zealand) _ The first sunrise of the
new millennium will be a cold and lonely moment as the midnight sun
dips below the horizon near Dibble Glacier in Antarctica. At the
western edge of the international dateline, the Antarctic dawn will
take place 14 hours before the ball descends in Times Square, but
no one is likely to be there to see the century's first dawn. This
has touched off a competition among the islands of the South
Pacific for the claim of being the first inhabited place to witness
the first sunbeams of the future. By Seth Mydans.
</P>
