<P>
   EATWITH-KIDS _ WACO, Texas _ In today's fast-paced world, the
art of parents teaching their children manners and politeness at
the dinner table has been lost, some say. How kids behave in
fast-food establishments and other restaurants may not seem like
the most pressing social issue in America today, but
restaurant-industry experts say the trend toward eating out means
more and more Americans _ both young and old _ will be sharing the
same eating space in the years to come. That puts etiquette for all
age groups at a premium. (O'Brien, Waco Tribune-Service) MOVED
</P>
