<SLUG> BC-VIDEO-DEEPBLUE09-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Video of the week
 &HT;    By Steve Murray
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``Deep Blue Sea'' (R)
</P>
<P>
   People get chewed up real good in this gleefully brutal flick
about three genetically engineered supersharks and the folks they
treat like party snacks.
</P>
<P>
   In case you care, the humans include Samuel L. Jackson, LL Cool
J, Saffron Burroughs and Thomas Jane. They're stuck on a sinking
research facility, but death by drowning would be preferable to
death by digestion as the huge makos get loose inside the flooded
wreck.
</P>
<P>
   Director Renny Harlin brings his usual hyper-drive direction to
the bloody action. The movie is smart enough to both honor and
break the rules of the horror genre, so you never know exactly when
the next scare will hit you. Sure, it's junk, but it'll make you
jump.
</P>
<P>
   Grade: B-
</P>
<P>
   _Steve Murray writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
