   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MORSE-COLUMN (San Francisco) _ Eat first, dress warmly in
layers, wear good walking shoes and carry water. Those are the
official recommendations for people planning to celebrate the
arrival of the new millennium in three weeks. Here's a more useful
recommendation for millennium weekend: Put in a three-day supply of
champagne and beluga, or chips and brew, and stay home. By ROB
MORSE.
</P>
<P>
   LYNCH-COLUMN (Schenectady, N.Y.) _ Dan Marciniac was in Station
Two on State Street, doing paper work, when the call came in around
9:30 Sunday night. It was a 99. Schenectady firefighters see maybe
half a hundred 99s a year. When a 99 comes in, it means the fire is
big and mean and fully capable of killing you when you do battle
with it. By DAN LYNCH.
</P>
