<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Locate hard-to-find itemsBy Marylin Johnson
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Having trouble finding a particular item? We'll try to help you
locate it. But due to the volume of mail, we cannot track down
every request. Readers whose queries are answered in the column
will receive a blue-and-cream canvas Buyer's Edge tote bag. Write
us at Buyer's Edge Find It, Atlanta Journal-Constitution, P.O. Box
4689, Atlanta, GA 30302; e-mail us at buyersedge(at)ajc.com (please
include your name, the city you live in and daytime phone number);
or call 404-582-7642.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Recently I read an article regarding a new perfume called
Southernness. Could you please tell me where and when this
particular perfume will be available.
</P>
<P>
   _ Peggie Crumley, Fayetteville, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: This scent of the South is a blend of flora from 12 Southern
states. Taking a chance on the obvious, we quickly found the
fragrance on the Web at www.southernness.com. A 3.4-ounce bottle is
$42. It also comes in the form of powders, body lotion, talc and
sachet. Southernness is the creation of garden artist Benn Johnson
of Birmingham. Several years ago, Johnson decided he actually
wanted to smell one of his paintings. With the aid of French
perfumer Phillipe Lorson, he came up with the floral scent.
</P>
<P>
   A sampling of stores in Atlanta that carry the fragrance and
related items, includes: Parisian stores, the Atlanta History
Center's Museum Shop (404-814-4075), Ivy Rose in Stone Mountain
(770-413-1213), Shoppe of Vinings in Vinings (770-433-1690) and
Presents Requested in Alpharetta (770-664-6882). Items are priced
from $18-$45.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I am looking for a Pendleton shirt, which lasts me from 10-15
years.
</P>
<P>
   _ Walter Bryner, Douglasville, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: Pendleton Woolen Mills, a dyed-in-the-wool American company,
has been churning out men's shirts since 1924. The Portland,
Ore.-based company has been in business since the late 1800s when
it began producing wool blankets for neighboring Native American
tribes, and later clothing for men and women. Today, men's
Pendleton shirts come in 10 styles, in 75 exclusive patterns.
Prices start at about $61 for a wool shirt.
</P>
<P>
   Shop at home by visiting the company's Web site:
www.pendleton-usa.com. Click on shopping basket, then menswear
gifts and stock up. You can also buy these classics in Atlanta at
Vinings Pendleton, 4300 Paces Ferry Road N.W., Suite 255
(770-384-1777) and Pendleton of Dunwoody, 5488 Chamblee Dunwoody
Road, Suite 8 (770-698-8005).
</P>
<P>
   Q: Until recently I could buy stollen imported from Germany at
several Atlanta stores. Now I can't find it anywhere. Could you
find me a source?
</P>
<P>
   _ Daryl H. Hiller, Dunwoody, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: This traditional Christmas yeast bread is filled with dried
fruits, raisins, almonds and spices and iced with a sugar frosting.
A yummy confection, it dates to the Middle Ages. We found stollen
on the Internet by using the search engine Yahoo, then typing in
``stollen,'' ``German'' and ``bread.'' One Web source is www
</P>
<P>
   .fancyfoods.com/stollen. Made by Rossbach Specialty Food _ under
the Elzer name _ its stollen is $5.50 for a 1-pound, 10.4-ounce
loaf. This company's stollen is also available in Wal-Mart
Supercenter stores in Georgia for $3.99.
</P>
<P>
   Another Web source is www.sbakingco.com/products/stollen. The
Santa Barbara Baking Co. soaks its stollen in rum for 24 hours
before baking. The price for a 1 1/2-pound loaf is $12.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I am interested in purchasing wooden Tinker Toys like the
ones my brother and I played with as children. I have seen the
plastic versions in stores but they seem to be larger.
</P>
<P>
   _ Sharon Salsberry, Marietta, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: Tinker, doodle, fiddle! Your beloved wooden rod-and-connector
toy is no longer being made by Playskool, a division of Hasbro.
However, a Texas manufacturer, Toys-N-Things (T-N-T) International,
has come out with Fiddlestix, an alternative construction set of
rods, spools, balls, wheels and squares. A spokesman for T-N-T told
us Fiddlestix are manufactured in the same circa 1860s Northeast
wood-working factory that made the original sets for Hasbro. The
company does not have the rights to the Tinker Toy name; hence, the
Fiddlestix moniker.
</P>
<P>
   You can purchase Fiddlestix on the Internet at www
</P>
<P>
   .somedayisle.com/toys/constrct
</P>
<P>
   /tinker.htm. A 120-piece wooden set is $58. We discovered this
site by using the search engine Dogpile and typing in ``tinker
toys.'' We scrolled through the offerings until we found this link.
You can also call 1-800-388-6313 and order the toy.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I need to know where to buy a medical alert bracelet. They
used to be advertised, but now I can't find them.
</P>
<P>
   _ Virginia Lynch, Marietta, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: This life-saving jewelry makes a great gift for a loved one.
We searched the Internet for ``medical alert bracelet'' on the
search engine Yahoo, then followed the links to two sites.
</P>
<P>
   One is www.oneida-medical-jewelry.com. Oneida Nameplate Co. in
Manchester, Iowa, makes engraved medical bracelets as well as
charms and necklaces in stainless steel, enamel, 24k gold and Black
Hills gold. All items bear the universal medical alert symbol and
are engraved with your medical and contact information. Prices for
bracelets range from $15.95 to $207.95; charms and necklaces range
from $5.95-$167.95. Or call 319-925-2586 to order the jewelry.
</P>
<P>
   The SOS medical locket, made by Slim Line Products, is also
available online at www.soalert.com. It's available as a necklace,
bracelet, sneaker tag, key chain and children's wristband in
silvertone stainless steel and gold-plated stainless steel, ranging
from $35-$79.50. The locket is embossed with the universal medical
alert symbol that tells persons to look inside for vital
information _ folded inside on paper. Call 1-800-224-3535 to order
this jewelry.
</P>
<P>
   _ Contributing: Michelle C. Brooks
</P>
<P>
   Marylin Johnson writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
