 (Repeating as part of a weekly roundup of computer features)   &HT;    Bagging online bargains
 &HT;    (Package includes ONLINE-SHOPPING, ONLINE-DEALS, ONLINE-LISTS,
ONLINE-COLUMN.)
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Where to begin? We've compiled a list of some interesting places
to shop online. In addition to those listed here, many name-brand
retailers and manufacturers have Web sites; they're usually pretty
easy to find.
</P>
<P>
   Shoppers' services
</P>
<P>
   www.bizrate.com: Rates online stores; helps customers get good
deals
</P>
<P>
   www.respond.com: Helps shoppers locate particular items
</P>
<P>
   www.shoponline123.com: Rates shopping sites; gives online
shopping tips
</P>
<P>
   www.flooz.com: ``World's first online gift currency''
</P>
<P>
   www.webcertificate.com: Online gift certificates
</P>
<P>
   www.rocketcash.com: Allows kids to buy online without a credit
card
</P>
<P>
   www.giftpoint.com: Allows you to purchase gift certificates from
many online stores. Or you can purchase a generic certificate that
allows your recipient to select a certificate from any store she
likes.
</P>
<P>
   www.wishlist.com, www.wishclick.com, and www.OhIWish.com: Gift
registries.
</P>
<P>
   Accessories
</P>
<P>
   www.luggageonline.com: Luggage.
</P>
<P>
   www.winksmile.com: Vintage jewelry, accessories.
</P>
<P>
   www.glamnet.com: Accessories from faux fur to rhinestones.
</P>
<P>
   www.ties.com: Fun tie site featuring a museum.
</P>
<P>
   www.sunglasssite.com: Many name brands.
</P>
