 (Repeating as part of a weekly roundup of computer features)   &HT;    But wait, there's more!
 &HT;    (Package includes ONLINE-SHOPPING, ONLINE-DEALS, ONLINE-LISTS,
ONLINE-COLUMN.)
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Online merchants want your business, and they're going to great
lengths to get it. The Web is rife with offers of free this and
free that. Shipping, merchandise, dollars off _ merchants will give
a lot to get you to shop with them. Here is a small sampling of the
deals that await.
</P>
<P>
   _ At www.greengrassgolf. com, they'll send you a free (you pay
shipping) putter, just for visiting their site and filling out a
form.
</P>
<P>
   _ www.CDNOW.com offers 30 percent off music and free shipping
when you buy three or more items.
</P>
<P>
   _ 10 percent off holiday cookbooks at www.amazon.com.
</P>
<P>
   _ Free shipping at www.bid.com.
</P>
<P>
   _ Fossil.com offers free two-day shipping and mousepad with
every order.
</P>
<P>
   _ www.ibeauty.com offers free shipping and gift wrapping.
</P>
<P>
   _ Drugstore.com offers a free gift with purchase.
</P>
<P>
   _ Bluefly.com offers free shipping until Christmas.
</P>
<P>
   _ www.smartkidstoys.com offers free gift wrapping.
</P>
<P>
   _ Delias.com offers free shipping on orders over $40.
</P>
<P>
   _ A $75 purchase at eToys.com gets you a $10 gift certificate
for another store.
</P>
<P>
   _ Sign up now at Living.com and save $100 off your first order
over $500.
</P>
<P>
   _ Electricwish.com ships for free.
</P>
<P>
   _ Familywonder.com offers a free CD or video (you pay shipping).
No purchase necessary.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
