<HEADLINE>
`NO POPERY,' SAYS THE U.S. CONGRESS 
</HEADLINE>
   (Commentary)  
 &HT;    
 &HT;    (To purchase this ``separate buy'' article from the New York
Times Syndicate please contact syndicate sales representative DEBRA
WEYDERT at 732-390-4480)
 &HT;    
 By DIANA BUTLER BASS  
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features)  
 &HT;    
 &HT;    In the 19th century, ``no popery'' was a popular political
slogan in the United States. Because the nation's Protestant
