<HEADLINE>
TEEN PITCHER HAD A HARD TIME
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q:.MDNM/ Is Brien Taylor, the teen-age pitcher signed by the
Yankees around 10 years ago, still trying to reach the major
leagues? _ R.C., Thompson, Conn.
</P>
<P>
   A:.MDNM/ Taylor, who was 19 when he was first pick in the 1991
amateur draft, worked out with a Class A team of the Cleveland
Indians in August.
</P>
<P>
   The New York Yankees gave Taylor a record $1.55 million bonus in
1991 but let him become a free agent in 1998. He was signed to a
minor league contract by the Seattle Mariners and then released in
June.
</P>
<P>
   Two years after being drafted, Taylor got into a bar fight with
a childhood friend and injured his throwing shoulder. His
minor-league record over the past three seasons is 1-10.
</P>
<P>
   Q:.MDNM/ I have a story about working at General Motors I'd like
to tell Michael Moore, director of ``Roger and Me.'' Where can I
reach him? _ M.P., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A:.MDNM/ Write to Moore in care of Dog Eat Dog Films, 200 W.
57th St., No. 203, New York, NY 10019.
</P>
<P>
   Moore's weekly documentary series ``The Awful Truth'' airs on
the Bravo cable channel. The show, which was nominated for an Emmy,
begins its second season early next year.
</P>
<P>
   The documentary filmmaker also writes regularly on his Web site:
www.michaelmoore.com.
</P>
<P>
   Q:.MDNM/ Where can I find tapes of the TV series ``Twin Peaks?''
_ W.J.M., Worcester, Mass.
</P>
<P>
   A:.MDNM/ All episodes of ``Twin Peaks'' have been released on
video by WorldVision and can be found at stores such as Suncoast
Motion Picture Co. and Musicland.
</P>
<P>
   The series is divided into six four-hour-long tapes: episodes
1-5, 6-9, 10-14, 15-19, 20-24 and 25-29. There's also a boxed set
including all six tapes.
</P>
<P>
   The tapes contain one important difference from the original
broadcasts: The first episode contains a different ending that was
used in Europe. The U.S. version is not available on video at
present.
</P>
<P>
   Win-Mill Productions of Arlington publishes ``Wrapped in
Plastic,'' a fan magazine devoted to the show. To subscribe, send
$35.50 for first-class delivery or $29 for third-class to Win-Mill
Productions, 1912 E. Timberview Lane, Arlington, TX 76014.  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
