<HEADLINE>
(RESENDING TO CORRECT BYLINE) 
CHILD ACTRESS TREASURED FILM ROLE AS A HIGH SPOT IN LIFE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By PERRY STEWART 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Karolyn Grimes likes to say that she has been in bed with some
of the biggest stars in Hollywood.
</P>
<P>
   A juvenile actress in movies during the 1940s, Grimes shared the
screen with John Wayne, Bing Crosby, Cary Grant, David Niven and
other screen notables. Her most memorable portrayal was Zuzu,
daughter of Everyguy hero George Bailey in director Frank Capra's
classic 1946 film, ``It's a Wonderful Life.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I played everyone's daughter back then,'' Grimes said. ``It
seems they were always tucking me into bed.''
</P>
<P>
   Young Karolyn's screen father in ``Wonderful Life'' was, of
course, James Stewart. It's hardly a surprise that when Grimes
