NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR THURSDAY, DECEMBER 9
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Thursday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-LIVING-WAGE-LAWS-NYT (moved on Thursday, Nov. 18)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, Nov. 18,
about ``living wage'' ordinances, which raise pay for low-wage
workers and grant them benefits, misstated the purpose of money
raised by the Chamber of Commerce in Santa Monica, Calif., to fight
a proposed ordinance. The money is going to a general campaign, not
to support candidates in next year's City Council election.
</P>
<P>
   BC-CIR-DIGITAL-DARKROOM-ART-NYT (moved on Wednesday, Dec. 1)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, Dec. 1,
about photo editing software referred incorrectly to the abilities
of one program, PhotoGenetics, because its producer, Q-Research
provided an incomplete version. A review of the full program
appears today on Page 3 of Circuits.
</P>
