<HEADLINE>
RAIDERS, TITANS CLASH 
</HEADLINE>
  (jt) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   Oakland (6-6) at Tennessee (9-3)
</P>
<P>
   The Oakland season has been full of close, thrilling,
final-second finishes, and the Raiders know the array of emotions
in both the depth of defeat and the excitement of victory. This
will be another dramatic test that they are well-suited to win.
Gannon is hot, and his pair of backs, Tyrone Wheatley (677) and
Napoleon Kaufman (513) have Oakland leading the league in rushing
average per game (129.9). Tennessee, however, is undefeated at
home, and its defense gains an edge from the loud crowd.
</P>
<P>
   Jevon Kearse leads all rookies with 9.5 sacks. He will lead a
pass-rush brigade that forces Gannon mistakes. And watch Eddie
George outduel the Raiders' duo.
</P>
<P>
   Tennessee earns its first 10-victory season in six years.
</P>
<P>
   Titans, 24-17.
</P>
