   &QL; 
 &UR; NETRATINGS &LR;  _ Despite its underdog status in the Web-tracking
business, shares of Milpitas' NetRatings Inc. popped 64 percent, or
$11, to close at $28 yesterday in its first day of public trading.
NetRatings raised $68 million by selling 4 million shares at $17
each, up from the $14 to $16 range it had initially planned. By
Carol Emert
